    <section id="faq" class="faq section-bg">
        <div class="container" data-aos="fade-up">

            <div class="section-title">
                <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
                <p>"Health Information and Medical Conditions: Your Questions Answered"</p>
            </div>

            <div class="faq-list">
                <ul>
                    <li data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="100">
                        <i class="bx bx-help-circle icon-help"></i> <a data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#faq-list-1">Diabetes<i class="bx bx-chevron-down icon-show"></i><i class="bx bx-chevron-up icon-close"></i></a>
                        <div id="faq-list-1" class="collapse show" data-bs-parent=".faq-list">
                            <p>
                                Diabetes is a chronic condition that affects how your body processes glucose (sugar). There are two main types: Type 1 and Type 2. Type 1 is an autoimmune disease, while Type 2 is often related to lifestyle factors. Both types result in elevated blood sugar levels that, if not managed, can lead to serious health complications.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </li>

                    <li data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="200">
                        <i class="bx bx-help-circle icon-help"></i> <a data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#faq-list-2">Heart Disease<i class="bx bx-chevron-down icon-show"></i><i class="bx bx-chevron-up icon-close"></i></a>
                        <div id="faq-list-2" class="collapse" data-bs-parent=".faq-list">
                            <p>
                                Heart disease, also known as cardiovascular disease, includes conditions that affect the heart and blood vessels. You can reduce your risk by maintaining a healthy diet, exercising regularly, not smoking, and managing conditions like high blood pressure and high cholesterol.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </li>

                    <li data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="300">
                        <i class="bx bx-help-circle icon-help"></i> <a data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#faq-list-3">Arthritis<i class="bx bx-chevron-down icon-show"></i><i class="bx bx-chevron-up icon-close"></i></a>
                        <div id="faq-list-3" class="collapse" data-bs-parent=".faq-list">
                            <p>
                                Arthritis is a group of conditions characterized by joint inflammation. While there is no cure, treatments such as medication, physical therapy, and lifestyle modifications can help manage symptoms and improve quality of life.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </li>

                    <li data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="400">
                        <i class="bx bx-help-circle icon-help"></i> <a data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#faq-list-4">Asthma<i class="bx bx-chevron-down icon-show"></i><i class="bx bx-chevron-up icon-close"></i></a>
                        <div id="faq-list-4" class="collapse" data-bs-parent=".faq-list">
                            <p>
                                Asthma attacks can be triggered by allergens like pollen or dust, respiratory infections, exercise, cold air, or exposure to irritants like smoke. Identifying and avoiding triggers is essential in asthma management.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </li>

                    <li data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="500">
                        <i class="bx bx-help-circle icon-help"></i> <a data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#faq-list-5">Alzheimer's Disease<i class="bx bx-chevron-down icon-show"></i><i class="bx bx-chevron-up icon-close"></i></a>
                        <div id="faq-list-5" class="collapse" data-bs-parent=".faq-list">
                            <p>
                                While there is no cure, research suggests that a healthy lifestyle with regular exercise, a balanced diet, and mental stimulation can help lower the risk or slow the progression of Alzheimer's disease.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </li>

                    <li data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="600">
                        <i class="bx bx-help-circle icon-help"></i> <a data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#faq-list-6">Chronic Kidney Disease<i class="bx bx-chevron-down icon-show"></i><i class="bx bx-chevron-up icon-close"></i></a>
                        <div id="faq-list-6" class="collapse" data-bs-parent=".faq-list">
                            <p>
                                Common causes of chronic kidney disease include diabetes, high blood pressure, and long-term use of certain medications. Early detection and management are crucial in slowing its progression.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </li>

                    <li data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="700">
                        <i class="bx bx-help-circle icon-help"></i> <a data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#faq-list-7">Crohn's Disease<i class="bx bx-chevron-down icon-show"></i><i class="bx bx-chevron-up icon-close"></i></a>
                        <div id="faq-list-7" class="collapse" data-bs-parent=".faq-list">
                            <p>
                                There isn't a one-size-fits-all diet for Crohn's, but some individuals find relief by avoiding trigger foods and following a low-residue or low-FODMAP diet. Consulting a dietitian can help tailor a diet plan to specific needs.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </li>

                    <li data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="800">
                        <i class="bx bx-help-circle icon-help"></i> <a data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#faq-list-8">COPD<i class="bx bx-chevron-down icon-show"></i><i class="bx bx-chevron-up icon-close"></i></a>
                        <div id="faq-list-8" class="collapse" data-bs-parent=".faq-list">
                            <p>
                                While COPD is not reversible, various treatments, including medication, oxygen therapy, and pulmonary rehabilitation, can help manage symptoms and improve quality of life.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </li>

                    <li data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="900">
                        <i class="bx bx-help-circle icon-help"></i> <a data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#faq-list-9">Multiple Sclerosis<i class="bx bx-chevron-down icon-show"></i><i class="bx bx-chevron-up icon-close"></i></a>
                        <div id="faq-list-9" class="collapse" data-bs-parent=".faq-list">
                            <p>
                                MS has a genetic component, but it's not directly inherited. A family history may slightly increase the risk, but other factors, like environmental and immune system factors, also play a role in its development.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </li>

                    <li data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="1000">
                        <i class="bx bx-help-circle icon-help"></i> <a data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#faq-list-10">Rheumatoid Arthritis<i class="bx bx-chevron-down icon-show"></i><i class="bx bx-chevron-up icon-close"></i></a>
                        <div id="faq-list-10" class="collapse" data-bs-parent=".faq-list">
                            <p>
                                Yes, rheumatoid arthritis can impact other organs, such as the heart, lungs, and eyes. It's important to work with a healthcare team to manage the disease comprehensively.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </li>

                    <li data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="1100">
                        <i class="bx bx-help-circle icon-help"></i> <a data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#faq-list-11">Osteoporosis<i class="bx bx-chevron-down icon-show"></i><i class="bx bx-chevron-up icon-close"></i></a>
                        <div id="faq-list-11" class="collapse" data-bs-parent=".faq-list">
                            <p>
                                While osteoporosis can't always be completely prevented, lifestyle changes such as regular weight-bearing exercise, a diet rich in calcium and vitamin D, and not smoking can help reduce the risk of developing the condition.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </li>

                    <li data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="1200">
                        <i class="bx bx-help-circle icon-help"></i> <a data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#faq-list-12">Lupus<i class="bx bx-chevron-down icon-show"></i><i class="bx bx-chevron-up icon-close"></i></a>
                        <div id="faq-list-12" class="collapse" data-bs-parent=".faq-list">
                            <p>
                                The exact cause of lupus is unknown, and there is no cure. Treatment focuses on managing symptoms and preventing flares using medication and lifestyle changes.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </li>

                    <li data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="1300">
                        <i class="bx bx-help-circle icon-help"></i> <a data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#faq-list-13">Parkinson's Disease<i class="bx bx-chevron-down icon-show"></i><i class="bx bx-chevron-up icon-close"></i></a>
                        <div id="faq-list-13" class="collapse" data-bs-parent=".faq-list">
                            <p>
                                While there is a genetic component to Parkinson's, it's not typically directly inherited. The majority of cases are sporadic, with a combination of genetic and environmental factors contributing to the disease.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </li>

                    <li data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="1400">
                        <i class="bx bx-help-circle icon-help"></i> <a data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#faq-list-14">Psoriasis<i class="bx bx-chevron-down icon-show"></i><i class="bx bx-chevron-up icon-close"></i></a>
                        <div id="faq-list-14" class="collapse" data-bs-parent=".faq-list">
                            <p>
                                Psoriasis is not contagious; it's an autoimmune skin condition. It can be triggered by various factors, including genetics and environmental influences.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </li>

                    <li data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="1500">
                        <i class="bx bx-help-circle icon-help"></i> <a data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#faq-list-15">Hypertension (High Blood Pressure)<i class="bx bx-chevron-down icon-show"></i><i class="bx bx-chevron-up icon-close"></i></a>
                        <div id="faq-list-15" class="collapse" data-bs-parent=".faq-list">
                            <p>
                                Lifestyle changes such as a healthy diet, regular exercise, reducing salt intake, and managing stress can help lower and control high blood pressure. In some cases, medication may also be necessary.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </li>

                    <li data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="1600">
                        <i class="bx bx-help-circle icon-help"></i> <a data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#faq-list-16">Cystic Fibrosis<i class="bx bx-chevron-down icon-show"></i><i class="bx bx-chevron-up icon-close"></i></a>
                        <div id="faq-list-16" class="collapse" data-bs-parent=".faq-list">
                            <p>
                                Cystic fibrosis is managed with a combination of airway clearance techniques, medications, and nutritional support. Treatment plans are personalized based on the individual's needs.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </li>

                    <li data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="1700">
                        <i class="bx bx-help-circle icon-help"></i> <a data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#faq-list-17">HIV/AIDS<i class="bx bx-chevron-down icon-show"></i><i class="bx bx-chevron-up icon-close"></i></a>
                        <div id="faq-list-17" class="collapse" data-bs-parent=".faq-list">
                            <p>
                                Currently, there is no cure for HIV, but antiretroviral therapy (ART) can effectively control the virus and allow people with HIV to live long and healthy lives.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </li>

                    <li data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="1800">
                        <i class="bx bx-help-circle icon-help"></i> <a data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#faq-list-18">Migraine<i class="bx bx-chevron-down icon-show"></i><i class="bx bx-chevron-up icon-close"></i></a>
                        <div id="faq-list-18" class="collapse" data-bs-parent=".faq-list">
                            <p>
                                Migraine prevention may involve identifying and avoiding triggers, making lifestyle changes, and taking medication as prescribed. Not all migraines can be prevented, but their frequency and severity can often be reduced.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </li>

                    <li data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="1900">
                        <i class="bx bx-help-circle icon-help"></i> <a data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#faq-list-19">Endometriosis<i class="bx bx-chevron-down icon-show"></i><i class="bx bx-chevron-up icon-close"></i></a>
                        <div id="faq-list-19" class="collapse" data-bs-parent=".faq-list">
                            <p>
                                Endometriosis can impact fertility, but not every individual with endometriosis experiences infertility. Treatments are available to help manage symptoms and improve fertility in some cases.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </li>

                    <li data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="2000">
                        <i class="bx bx-help-circle icon-help"></i> <a data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#faq-list-20">Osteoarthritis<i class="bx bx-chevron-down icon-show"></i><i class="bx bx-chevron-up icon-close"></i></a>
                        <div id="faq-list-20" class="collapse" data-bs-parent=".faq-list">
                            <p>
                                Osteoarthritis is primarily a wear-and-tear condition that affects joint cartilage, while rheumatoid arthritis is an autoimmune disease that causes inflammation and joint damage. Their causes, treatments, and progression patterns are different.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </li>
                </ul>
